
    BIE - Bugzilla Inline Editor

Inline Editor is extension to Bugzilla reporting system. Inline Editor enables batch editing of bugs by making list of bugs resulting from bug search editable. Extension is parametrised so that user can select from group of fields, which fields are editable in bug list.

    INSTALLATION

Install extension by extracting files from archive. Switch to 'extension' directory below Bugzilla root directory and extract files from archive.

Patch the core Bugzilla with patch file. Copy patch file into Bugzilla root directory. Switch into Bugzilla root directory and run patching with command: 
patch -p1 < bie_into_bz_v3_6_2.patch

